<div class="container">
<h1>History</h1>
<ul>
	<li>Named "folk football", Football originated in England with few rules in the 1800's.</li><br>
	<li>The University of Cambridge tried to regulate the rules in 1843.</li><br>
	<li>Since there were 2 'footballs' (rugby and fútbol), the FA prohibited the handling of the ball in football to avoid confusion.</li><br>
	<li>FIFA (Fédération Internationale de Football Association) was founded in the early 20th century by the football associations of <br>Belgium, Denmark, France, the Netherlands, Spain, Sweden, and Switzerland as the sport had spread out through Europe.</li><br>
	<li>Until the 1970's, most countries outside of northern Europe couldn't play in the World Cup. This was the case until a Brazilian became president of FIFA.</li><br>
	<li>Globalization continued and an estimated 3.575 billion watched the Qatar World Cup 2022 final (Argentina vs France). </li><br>
</ul>
</div>
</body>
</html>